<p class="blogheader"><A NAME="JsEssentials"><u>JavaScript Essentials</u></A></p>
	<p class="smaller">-24th July 2014<br/><br/></p>
<p>
<b>Here follows</b> some simple fiddles on jsfiddle.net that display some basics in JavaScript.
On the first row, first cell, we see an example of an custom error handler and examples on how numbers are treated in comparison to numbers as text. Read the comments for more infomation.
Forward to the the second cell on the right, first row, shows how to create custom exceptions, use them to validate input and throw them as a response to invalid values.
On the second row, first cell to the left, we see object oriented JavaScript being examplified.  To the right on the second row, we see object oriented JavaScript again, this time testing the scope and availability of variables.
<br/><br/>
